    <p style="margin-bottom: 10px; color:#444;">
    I don’t have an official record of any of my art. I know that I’ve been interested in photography ever since I was a Cub Scout. That was one of the very first things I defined during those years. My interest in art has only taken a very strong effect within the past two years. I have done many different types of art and my second art form that I figured out that I loved was calligraphy. I got pretty good at it for a little while although I had a very shaky hand after a while I started getting bored with calligraphy and moved onto graffiti love the style and colors of graffiti and actually did pretty well on it. My pieces were normally simple, either bubbles or an attempt at wild style. The graffiti trend lasted for quite a while. I would buy books on it. I would buy paint pens on for it. I would buy sketchbook for it. 
</p>

